  <p>
   The sign "close-by-a-hair" means: "That was a close 
			one!"
   <br/>
  </p>
  <p>
   Reach up and grab an imaginary hair on the side of your upper forehead.  
  Using and extremely quick arching movement pull the hair out and then move it 
  downward a few inches.
  </p>
  <p>
   <img border="0" height="239" src="/images/close-1.jpg" width="241"/>
   <img border="0" height="239" src="/images/close-2.jpg" width="241"/>
   <img border="0" height="239" src="/images/close-3.jpg" width="241"/>
   <img border="0" height="239" src="/images/close-4.jpg" width="241"/>
   <img border="0" height="239" src="/images/close-5.jpg" width="241"/>
  </p>
  <p>
  </p>
  <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
  <p>
   "BY-A-HAIR" is an "
   <a href="../../pages-layout/idioms.htm">
    ASL 
			idiom
   </a>
   ." The sign appears to depict the "pulling of a hair" but 
			in actuality conveys the meaning of "nearly," "almost," "that was a 
			close one," and "narrowly escaped a negative happening."
  </p>
